Phase 2: Onboarding (ONB)
This phase focuses on transitioning the accepted candidate to an active employee, ensuring compliance, resource allocation, and initial payroll setup.

Step	Requirement ID	User Story Summary / Action


1. Setup & Checklist	ONB-001	HR Manager creates onboarding task checklists.


2. Profile Creation	ONB-002	HR Manager accesses signed contract detail to create an employee profile.


3. Document Collection	ONB-007	New Hire uploads compliance documents (e.g., ID, certifications).


4. Resource Reservation	ONB-012	HR Employee reserves and tracks equipment, desk and access cards.


5. System Access	ONB-009	System Admin provisions system access (payroll, email, internal systems).
	ONB-013	HR Manager ensures automated account provisioning on start date and scheduled revocation on exit.

6. New Hire Tracking	ONB-004	New Hire views onboarding steps in a tracker.
	ONB-005	New Hire receives reminders and notifications.

7. Payroll Initiation	ONB-018	HR Manager initiates system to automatically handle payroll initiation based on contract signing.
	ONB-019	HR Manager initiates system to automatically process signing bonuses.




Phase II: Onboarding (Integration & Provisioning)


8. Profile Creation & Checklist

HR Manager

Create onboarding task checklists [ONB-001]; access signed contract to create employee profile [ONB-002].	US: ONB-001, ONB-002. BR: Triggered by offer acceptance; checklists customizable.

Output: Employee Profile (Active); Onboarding Checklist (Activated).

Data Flow: Uses signed contract data from Recruitment; outputs to Employee Profile.



9. Compliance & Tracking

New Hire

View onboarding tracker [ONB-004]; receive reminders [ONB-005]; upload compliance documents [ONB-007].	US: ONB-004, ONB-005, ONB-007. BR: Tracker and reminders required; documents stored securely.

Output: Documents Uploaded (Stored); Task Progress Updated.

Data Flow: Documents stored in Employee Profile.



10. Resource Provisioning

HR Employee / System Admin

Reserve and track equipment [ONB-012]; provision secure system access [ONB-009].	US: ONB-012, ONB-009. BR: IT and payroll access automated; all resources tracked.

Output: Access Granted; Equipment Reserved.

Data Flow: Logged for audit; feeds Time Management (clock access).



11. Payroll Initiation & Benefits

HR Manager

Automate payroll initiation upon contract signing [ONB-018]; process signing bonuses [ONB-019].	US: ONB-018, ONB-019. BR: Bonuses treated as distinct payroll components; payroll trigger automatic.

Output: Payroll Initiation Triggered; Bonus Processed.

Data Flow: Triggers payroll processing steps (REQ-PY-23, REQ-PY-27).



12. Scheduled Access Management

HR Manager / System Admin

Schedule automatic provisioning and revocation of accounts [ONB-013].	US: ONB-013. BR: Provisioning and security must be consistent.

Output: Scheduled Revocation Flag.

Data Flow: Info passed to Offboarding (OFF-007) for security control.


